46:58.240 --> 47:02.240
Well, if it God does exist, it seems you've got notes.

47:05.440 --> 47:07.600
That's all very interesting,

47:07.600 --> 47:13.600
but it doesn't explain why the anti-gender movement just doesn't listen.

47:13.600 --> 47:16.400
Remember back at the start when we learned about the school board

47:16.400 --> 47:19.680
who turned down $10,000 of free money?

47:19.680 --> 47:22.320
Remember how the same misunderstandings of Butler's work

47:22.320 --> 47:24.000
have circulated for decades?

47:24.000 --> 47:26.400
Remember the insistence that the law was made

47:27.120 --> 47:29.200
that the law must have a strict definition of women,

47:29.200 --> 47:30.880
even though we know that's not true?

47:30.880 --> 47:32.880
Remember all those unevidence conspiracies

47:32.880 --> 47:36.720
about the trans deep state and secret UN plots?

47:36.720 --> 47:40.480
There's something else too that's very interesting.

47:41.280 --> 47:45.120
The language that the anti-gender movement uses is very

47:46.000 --> 47:52.720
actioning, threat, infiltration, danger, bullying, silencing, censorship,

47:52.720 --> 47:54.560
a comparison to nuclear weapons.

47:55.200 --> 47:56.560
It's not just that they're not listening.

47:57.280 --> 47:58.800
When they're invited to listen,

47:59.520 --> 48:02.080
it seems like that makes them feel as if they're under attack.

48:03.040 --> 48:04.720
And Butler has an explanation for this.

48:05.600 --> 48:10.320
They say that these people are caught in a phantasm.

48:11.040 --> 48:14.240
Phantasm is a technical philosophy term

48:14.240 --> 48:17.760
for a particular way of misinterpreting the world

48:17.760 --> 48:20.560
by projecting your feelings onto it.

48:21.280 --> 48:24.400
Philosopher Michael Nass says that it's a prism

48:24.400 --> 48:28.080
that refracts an as-if into an as-so.

48:28.880 --> 48:32.000
For example, the presence of a trans person

48:32.000 --> 48:33.920
with a penis in a public bathroom

48:33.920 --> 48:38.000
makes me feel as if I am under attack becomes...

48:41.360 --> 48:43.200
I am under attack.

48:43.920 --> 48:48.400
People use phantasms to avoid cognitive dissonance

48:48.400 --> 48:50.160
in the face of anxiety.

48:50.640 --> 48:53.360
For example, literature professor Darren Tenev

48:53.360 --> 48:56.000
says we use them to help us confront death.

48:56.880 --> 48:58.720
Normally, we don't want to think about our own deaths.

48:58.720 --> 49:00.080
It makes us anxious.

49:00.080 --> 49:02.560
So when we picture our own funerals

49:02.560 --> 49:05.760
and what we would want to happen to our remains,

49:05.760 --> 49:07.680
we imagine ourselves as being gone,

49:08.320 --> 49:10.320
but also kind of still around.

49:10.320 --> 49:13.360
Like, oh, I'd love to be buried somewhere that has a nice view.

49:15.040 --> 49:16.160
Well, why?

49:16.160 --> 49:18.400
You're not going to be there to enjoy it by definition.

49:18.400 --> 49:19.760
That's a contradictory dream.

49:20.720 --> 49:23.840
But the phantasm contains that contradiction

49:24.400 --> 49:26.960
and soothes our anxiety.

49:26.960 --> 49:29.600
It is as if I will still be there.

49:32.720 --> 49:34.640
I will still be there.

49:35.360 --> 49:37.360
What is characteristic of phantasms

49:37.360 --> 49:38.800
is that they are placed

49:38.800 --> 49:41.520
and place what could be called the subject of phantasm

49:42.160 --> 49:44.480
on both sides of a border,

49:44.480 --> 49:47.040
a boundary, a limit, a frontier.

49:47.040 --> 49:49.440
When there is a border, a limitation,

49:50.000 --> 49:53.040
the phantasm lets one on the other side

49:53.040 --> 49:55.600
and not only provides a contraband access

49:55.600 --> 49:56.560
through the border,

49:56.560 --> 49:59.840
but also keeps one on both sides at the same time.

49:59.840 --> 50:02.800
There is no logic of the phantasm.

50:02.800 --> 50:04.560
The phantasm is phantasm

50:04.560 --> 50:08.160
because it allows one to stand on both sides of a border,

50:08.160 --> 50:09.280
for example,

50:09.280 --> 50:12.160
allowing one to imagine one's own corpse

50:12.160 --> 50:13.760
while still being alive.

50:14.320 --> 50:16.960
Like he says, there's no logic to this.

50:17.520 --> 50:20.960
It's an exercise in trying to not make sense

50:20.960 --> 50:22.800
because you can't handle the conclusions

50:22.800 --> 50:24.240
that you would reach if you did.

50:24.880 --> 50:26.880
That's why people caught in a phantasm

50:26.880 --> 50:28.320
will throw out all kinds of claims

50:28.320 --> 50:30.720
that it doesn't really seem like they've thought through

50:30.720 --> 50:32.400
or have any evidence for

50:32.400 --> 50:33.840
and when questioned on it,

50:33.840 --> 50:35.600
they'll say you're attacking me

50:35.600 --> 50:38.320
because they're trying really hard

50:38.320 --> 50:41.520
to not think something.

50:41.520 --> 50:43.520
But what exactly?

50:43.520 --> 50:44.800
What is the thing

50:44.800 --> 50:46.960
that the anti-gender movement doesn't want to think?

50:48.880 --> 50:51.680
Well, it'll probably be different

50:51.680 --> 50:52.880
for different individuals.

50:53.920 --> 50:56.880
J.K. Rowling has been massively radicalized

50:56.880 --> 50:58.800
into the movement in the last few years.

50:58.800 --> 51:00.400
She's made a lot of very weird

51:00.400 --> 51:02.320
and false claims about trans people

51:02.320 --> 51:04.720
and gotten very aggressive when challenged.

51:05.520 --> 51:07.840
People have speculated about her trauma,

51:07.840 --> 51:08.800
maybe causing that,

51:08.800 --> 51:11.040
but as a woman who's also survived

51:11.040 --> 51:12.000
an abusive relationship,

51:12.800 --> 51:14.160
that kind of public speculation

51:14.160 --> 51:16.240
has always felt a little bit gross to me.

51:17.120 --> 51:19.840
I don't want to do armchair psychology on anyone,

51:19.840 --> 51:21.600
even though I'm sure plenty of people

51:21.600 --> 51:22.720
would love to do some on me.

51:23.600 --> 51:26.320
It's just not the philosophy cheap way.

51:26.320 --> 51:29.200
So maybe we can ask a more general version

51:29.200 --> 51:30.400
of this same question.

51:31.120 --> 51:33.520
Why are phantasms catching on?

51:34.160 --> 51:35.440
And not just about this topic,

51:35.440 --> 51:36.960
but all sorts of things.

51:36.960 --> 51:38.080
On the previous episode,

51:38.080 --> 51:41.040
we talked about 15-minute city conspiracy theories

51:41.040 --> 51:43.040
and there's QAnon and conspiracies

51:43.040 --> 51:44.480
about the royal family.

51:44.480 --> 51:46.560
Sometimes the way that Zionists talk about

51:46.560 --> 51:48.880
Palestinians has a touch of the phantasma about it,

51:48.880 --> 51:51.280
as some Jewish scholars have noted.

51:51.280 --> 51:53.440
This is a really big issue

51:53.440 --> 51:55.040
and it would be great if we could sort

51:55.040 --> 51:56.400
the whole gender thing out

51:56.400 --> 51:59.280
because we've got a lot of real problems to deal with.

51:59.280 --> 52:01.840
We don't have time to be fighting imaginary ones.

52:04.640 --> 52:08.640
Oh, Graf and Korolchuk say

52:09.280 --> 52:11.680
there really are a lot of problems in the world.

52:12.400 --> 52:14.160
And a lot of them are systemic.

52:14.880 --> 52:16.560
A lot of women really are devalued.

52:16.560 --> 52:18.080
A lot of children really are living

52:18.080 --> 52:20.800
in an increasingly dangerous and warming world.

52:20.800 --> 52:23.120
A lot of people really do rely on their families

52:23.120 --> 52:25.040
to protect them from big institutions

52:25.040 --> 52:26.240
and economic forces

52:26.240 --> 52:28.400
that really will trample every tradition

52:28.400 --> 52:31.600
and really do dissolve everything into money.

52:31.600 --> 52:34.480
According to them, the anti-gender phantasm

52:34.480 --> 52:38.160
is an attempt to criticize the effects of capitalism

52:38.960 --> 52:42.160
without naming capitalism as the problem.

52:43.040 --> 52:45.360
People see the bad results of the system that we have,

52:46.160 --> 52:48.160
but they're invested in those same systems

52:48.720 --> 52:51.360
and so the solutions become unthinkable.

52:51.920 --> 52:53.600
Their criticisms have to be expressed

52:53.600 --> 52:56.800
as a kind of moral criticism.

52:58.080 --> 53:01.200
Anti-genderism is the socialism of fools

53:02.160 --> 53:03.680
and the feminism of fools

53:04.720 --> 53:07.280
and the anti-colonialism of fools.

53:07.280 --> 53:09.280
The anti-gender movement is so effective

53:09.280 --> 53:10.480
in attracting mass support

53:10.480 --> 53:12.400
because it is structured and legitimized

53:12.400 --> 53:15.680
as a conservative response to the excesses of neoliberalism.

53:16.560 --> 53:18.000
A crucial source of anxiety

53:18.000 --> 53:21.280
is the rampant individualism of contemporary culture,

53:21.280 --> 53:22.560
the erosion of community

53:22.560 --> 53:24.480
and growing instability of everyday life.

53:25.440 --> 53:26.880
Opponents of gender ideology

53:26.880 --> 53:29.440
attribute these trends to the influence of feminism

53:29.440 --> 53:30.640
and the sexual revolution.

53:31.360 --> 53:33.200
Anti-genderism conflates gender

53:33.200 --> 53:35.040
with those aspects of capitalism

53:35.040 --> 53:36.400
that are most frustrating

53:36.400 --> 53:38.800
to members of the working and lower middle class,

53:38.800 --> 53:40.960
especially to parents and would-be parents,

53:40.960 --> 53:42.880
precarity and the crisis of care

53:42.880 --> 53:45.120
resulting from unequal distribution of wealth.

53:45.920 --> 53:48.640
Instead of naming the problem in economic terms

53:48.640 --> 53:51.120
as injustice and exploitation,

53:51.120 --> 53:54.240
anti-genderism presents the world of capitalism's winners

53:54.240 --> 53:57.120
as degenerate and morally corrupt.

53:57.120 --> 54:00.080
And here's where we tie it all together

54:00.720 --> 54:04.000
and bring it back to Judith Butler.

54:04.720 --> 54:08.240
When the anti-gender movement say that gender is an ideology

54:08.240 --> 54:10.320
and sex is a fixed point,

54:10.320 --> 54:13.760
we now understand they aren't making an observation,

54:13.760 --> 54:15.680
they're making a demand.

54:16.480 --> 54:19.280
When they say that you can't change sex,

54:19.280 --> 54:22.640
they mean you shouldn't be allowed to

54:22.640 --> 54:24.720
because that would be dangerous,

54:24.720 --> 54:27.680
not the kind of danger that is proven with evidence,

54:27.680 --> 54:32.160
but the kind they want the state to posit and punish.

54:32.560 --> 54:35.360
What they want is morally righteous violence

54:35.360 --> 54:37.520
that restores an imaginary order

54:37.520 --> 54:39.920
because they are anxious about real problems

54:39.920 --> 54:42.720
that they cannot or will not think about,

54:42.720 --> 54:45.200
and so they can only glimpse those problems

54:45.200 --> 54:50.400
through the prism of unreality.

54:50.400 --> 54:53.920
The contradictory character of the phantasm

54:53.920 --> 54:56.640
allows it to contain whatever anxiety or fear

54:56.640 --> 54:59.200
that the anti-gender ideology wishes to stoke

54:59.200 --> 55:00.400
for its own purposes,

55:00.800 --> 55:02.960
without having to make any of it cohere.

55:02.960 --> 55:06.560
Depending on the anxieties circulating in a particular region,

55:06.560 --> 55:09.360
gender can be figured as Marxist or capitalist,

55:09.360 --> 55:13.200
tyranny or libertarianism, fascism or totalitarianism,

55:13.200 --> 55:16.400
a totalizing force, or an unwanted migrant.

55:16.400 --> 55:19.360
It is not that people are unmindful of the contradiction

55:19.360 --> 55:20.880
and need to be enlightened.

55:20.880 --> 55:23.760
No, the contradiction itself is what works,

55:23.760 --> 55:26.080
in effect emancipating people from the task

55:26.080 --> 55:28.000
of developing a rational position.

55:30.640 --> 55:34.000
Maybe it's because I'm older,

