59:00.560 --> 59:04.240
But here's some suggestions, maybe.

59:04.240 --> 59:07.920
If you're Catholic and you like buying little medals

59:07.920 --> 59:11.440
or rosaries or chuchkies, if you have relatives who do,

59:11.440 --> 59:12.960
maybe older relatives who do,

59:13.840 --> 59:16.960
you might like to double check where that money is going.

59:16.960 --> 59:18.560
If you happen to work in media,

59:18.720 --> 59:23.600
that all of this theory could have some practical applications for you,

59:23.600 --> 59:25.840
we might like to talk about anti-genderists

59:25.840 --> 59:29.120
the same way we talk about anti-vaxxers or climate deniers.

59:29.120 --> 59:33.200
For example, Mrs. X says this, which is false.

59:33.200 --> 59:36.800
Organization Y claims this, which is pseudoscience.

59:36.800 --> 59:38.800
Another thing that you might like to try

59:38.800 --> 59:41.680
is using the word cisgender.

59:41.680 --> 59:43.200
It was coined in the early 90s.

59:43.200 --> 59:45.520
It means not transgender.

59:45.520 --> 59:48.640
And the English language anti-gender movement hate it

59:48.640 --> 59:52.160
because it implies that trans people and cis people

59:52.160 --> 59:54.720
are both worth listening to.

59:55.440 --> 59:59.520
It resists objectification by putting us on an even playing field.

59:59.520 --> 01:00:02.720
Kind of like using the word straight or heterosexual

01:00:02.720 --> 01:00:04.320
instead of saying normal.

01:00:04.320 --> 01:00:08.400
Beyond that, Graf and Karl Schuch say we need to appreciate the fact

01:00:08.400 --> 01:00:12.320
that right-wing populism is criticizing capitalism,

01:00:12.320 --> 01:00:14.640
albeit in phantasmic terms.

01:00:14.640 --> 01:00:16.720
They say we should move beyond the old idea

01:00:16.720 --> 01:00:18.320
that the left are anti-capitalist

01:00:18.320 --> 01:00:20.720
and the right are always pro-market.

01:00:20.720 --> 01:00:23.200
Now some of them are, to be sure, but not all.

01:00:23.200 --> 01:00:25.440
They say that these days a lot of people on the right

01:00:25.440 --> 01:00:27.440
are actually criticizing capitalism

01:00:27.440 --> 01:00:30.080
even if they don't use that kind of language.

01:00:30.080 --> 01:00:33.040
And so sticking to the same old economic policies

01:00:33.040 --> 01:00:34.480
we've had for the last 40 years

01:00:34.480 --> 01:00:38.560
is leaving yourself wide open to those far right extremists.

01:00:39.200 --> 01:00:42.320
They also say that LGBTQ stuff and gender stuff

01:00:42.320 --> 01:00:45.600
can't really be separated from normal politics anymore

01:00:46.160 --> 01:00:48.400
because that's how a lot of people are engaging

01:00:48.400 --> 01:00:50.800
with normal politics these days.

01:00:50.800 --> 01:00:53.360
The anti-gender phantasm isn't the only thing

01:00:53.360 --> 01:00:55.520
powering the global right, to be sure,

01:00:55.520 --> 01:00:57.520
but it's big enough that it can't be ignored.

01:00:58.560 --> 01:01:01.360
Important lessons there for centrists, perhaps.

01:01:01.360 --> 01:01:05.040
They recommend a strategy called populist feminism

01:01:05.040 --> 01:01:08.800
which involves tapping into people's emotions in the moment.

01:01:08.800 --> 01:01:11.120
An example from the UK might be the group

01:01:11.120 --> 01:01:13.520
Sisters Uncut who've been very successful

01:01:13.520 --> 01:01:17.200
mobilizing a broad coalition against austerity,

01:01:17.200 --> 01:01:20.160
domestic violence cuts, police violence,

01:01:20.160 --> 01:01:21.760
prisons, health care segregation,

01:01:21.760 --> 01:01:23.280
arms sales to the Israeli government,

01:01:23.280 --> 01:01:24.720
and many other things

01:01:24.720 --> 01:01:27.040
because they recognize that all those forces

01:01:27.040 --> 01:01:29.200
disproportionately hurt women

01:01:29.200 --> 01:01:32.720
and therefore women can be brought together

01:01:32.720 --> 01:01:34.480
to protest against them

01:01:34.480 --> 01:01:37.600
if given the chance to express our feelings

01:01:37.600 --> 01:01:40.160
of hurt and righteous anger.

01:01:40.240 --> 01:01:42.320
There's many ways to be involved in a group like that

01:01:42.320 --> 01:01:44.160
from actually taking Barton demonstrations

01:01:44.160 --> 01:01:45.280
to donating money

01:01:45.280 --> 01:01:48.320
which again empowers a broad coalition.

01:01:48.320 --> 01:01:50.960
A broad coalition, a coalition of broads,

01:01:50.960 --> 01:01:54.240
dames, dime pieces, chicks, dolls, all standing together.

01:01:55.120 --> 01:01:55.920
Will it work?

01:01:58.240 --> 01:02:00.240
Well, join me at the end of the 21st century

01:02:00.240 --> 01:02:02.080
to see humanity's final scores.

01:02:02.080 --> 01:02:04.480
And now our second question.

01:02:05.520 --> 01:02:08.800
Can we reach people stuck in phantasms?

01:02:08.800 --> 01:02:11.280
